    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-07-05T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-07-05T05:00:00-05:00" n="395"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d395">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">357.AC/7–551: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Syria</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CCW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cannon</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d395fn1">Repeated for information to Tel Aviv.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Damascus</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-07-05T12:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 5, 1951—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6. Over past fortnight we have been deeply impressed by info from Damascus
                    diplomatic sources which seem to confirm Syrian charges <pb facs="0785" n="745"
                        xml:id="pg_745"/> to effect that Israeli have used intimidation and even
                    physical abuse to prevent Arabs at Shaab from declaring <gloss target="#t_TSO1"
                        >TSO</gloss> preference for return to Ghanameh and Baghara. Many Arab heads
                    of families especially landowners have not been available for questioning and
                    seem to have “disappeared”; as result intimidation others have withdrawn their
                    request to return. They are wretched and hopeless.</p>
                <p>We therefore wholly concur in point one <gloss target="#t_Depcirtel1"
                        >Depcirtel</gloss> July 2<note n="2" xml:id="d395fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_739">p. 739</ref>.</note> and
                    are convinced only way to enable <gloss target="#t_TSO1">TSO</gloss> ascertain
                    Arabs’ true wishes is to return them all to demilitarized zone forthwith wholly
                    removed from Israel jurisdiction and control. In this way something could be
                    done to counteract Syrian disillusionment with <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>
                    resolution. We see definite danger in growing sentiment in Arab states this
                    resolution only another manifestation venality of <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                        >UN</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Other comments on <gloss target="#t_reftel1">reftel</gloss> will fol.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d395fn3">With respect to further comments by the Embassy in Syria on
                        circular telegram 2 of July 2, see telegram 26 from Damascus, July 14, <ref
                            target="#pg_770">p. 770</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CCW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cannon</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
